article.headline: UMKC 86, Chicago St. 78
article.story: Kansas City, MO. (AP) -- Dee Ayuba had 20 points and a career-high seven assists in leading Missouri-Kansas City to an 86-78 nonconference win over Chicago State on Thursday. The victory broke a three-game losing streak for the Kangaroos (5-11), while the Cougars (5-14) lost their fifth straight. Ayuba had 14 points in the first half, with Brent Stephens providing most of the scoring for UMKC down the stretch. Stephens, who had 14 of his 19 points in the final 6:52 of the game, was 9-of-9 from the free throw line. UMKC led 79-69 with just under 3:30 to go before the Cougars went on a run to close the gap to 83-78 with 53 seconds left in the game. Three Kangaroo free throws provided the final margin. Alex Pledger, a 7-1 sophomore from New Zealand, scored a career-high 16 points and had 11 rebounds for UMKC. Quinton Day added 12 points for the Kangaroos. Chicago State was led by Michael Henderson with 21 points and 11 rebounds. John Cantrell had 16 points and David Holston and Royce Parran added 15 each for the Cougars.
